            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/shipments","startButtonLabel":"Tour Shipments","steps":[{"element":"[data-testid='new-shipment-btn']","popover":{"title":"New Shipment Button","description":"Click here to create a new shipment. You'll select a Sales Order first, then add line items by choosing from that order's open lines (quantity capped at what remains to ship), and optionally enter carrier and tracking information. The dialog uses a split layout: line items on the left, shipment details and notes on the right.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".filters-bar app-input","popover":{"title":"Search Shipments","description":"Search by shipment number, Sales Order number, customer name, carrier, or tracking number. Press Enter to apply the search. Results update in the table below.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".filters-bar app-select","popover":{"title":"Status Filter","description":"Filter shipments by their current status: Pending, Packed, Shipped, In Transit, Delivered, or Cancelled. Each status has a distinct color-coded chip in the table for quick identification.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"Shipments Table","description":"Click any row to open the shipment detail dialog. Columns include Shipment Number, SO Number, Customer, Status (color chip), Carrier, Tracking Number, Shipped Date, and Created date. Click column headers to sort. Use the gear icon to manage column visibility and order.","side":"top"}},{"element":"[data-testid='new-shipment-btn']","popover":{"title":"Creating a Shipment — Walkthrough","description":"When you click New Shipment, a dialog opens with a split layout. On the right sidebar, select the Sales Order first (required) — this drives everything else. On the left, you then add line items by choosing one of that order's open lines from the dropdown; the quantity prefills with what's left to ship and is capped there (you cannot exceed the remaining quantity). Click Add and each line appears in a table where you can remove it. Optionally enter Carrier, Tracking Number, Weight, Shipping Cost, and Notes. Save is disabled until you have at least one line item and a Sales Order selected.","side":"left"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"Shipment Detail View","description":"Clicking a row opens the detail dialog. It shows the shipment number, status chip, linked Sales Order (clickable), customer name, carrier info, tracking number, shipped/delivered dates, weight, shipping cost, notes, and all line items. Action buttons appear based on status: Mark Shipped (from Pending/Packed), Get Rates (carrier rate comparison), Track (loads tracking timeline), and Mark Delivered (from Shipped/In Transit). An activity timeline shows the full history of status changes and updates.","side":"top"}}]}"""
